Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20contenders%20for%20the%20post.%20The%20other%20one%20is%20Shambhu%20Prasad%20Acharya%2C%20a%20public%20health%20specialist%20from%20Nepal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fsoutheastasia%2Fabout%5C%22%3Eone%20of%20the%2011%20member%20states%20of%20the%20SEARO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20will%20vote%20in%20the%20polls.%20Quoting%20a%20Press%20Information%20Bureau%20statement%2C%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fi%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fworld%2Fwho-southeast-asia-post-modi-govts-support-for-sheikh-hasinas-daughter-triggers-worry%2Fcid%2F1968230%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20India%20has%20already%20indicated%20its%20support%20for%20the%20Bangladesh%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20daughter%20%E2%80%93%20a%20move%20that%20experts%20have%20termed%20as%20an%20instance%20of%20giving%20geopolitics%20greater%20importance%20over%20public%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWazed%20was%20prominently%20visible%20in%20the%20recently%20held%20G20%20Summit%20in%20New%20Delhi%20along%20with%20her%20mother.%20Bangladesh%20has%20already%20thanked%20India%20for%20its%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThree%20of%20the%20signatories%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20daughter%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20%E2%80%9Ctechnical%2C%20administrative%20or%20public%20health%20experience%E2%80%9D%20to%20head%20the%20office.%20Bangladesh%20had%20nominated%20her%20because%20she%20was%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20daughter%2C%20they%20claimed.%20This%20is%20one%20of%20the%20rare%20instances%20that%20the%20daughter%20of%20a%20serving%20prime%20minister%20is%20contesting%20to%20become%20head%20of%20the%20regional%20office%20of%20the%20WHO.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20Telegraph%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fi%3E%20attempt%20to%20get%20a%20response%20for%20her%20before%20publication%20of%20the%20report%20did%20not%20yield%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENepal%E2%80%99s%20candidate%2C%20Acharya%2C%20is%20a%20public%20health%20specialist%20with%20a%20PhD%20in%20public%20health%2C%20health%20policy%20and%20financing%20from%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20in%20the%20US.%20He%20has%20served%20the%20WHO%20for%20three%20decades%20in%20different%20capacities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWazed%20has%20an%20MSc%20degree%20in%20clinical%20psychology%20from%20Barry%20University%20(US).%20She%20has%20been%20a%20member%20of%20the%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20expert%20advisory%20panel%20on%20mental%20health%20for%20over%20nine%20years%2C%20and%20an%20adviser%20to%20the%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20director-general%20on%20mental%20health%20and%20autism%20for%20four%20years%2C%20according%20to%20her%20CV%2C%20submitted%20as%20part%20of%20the%20application%20for%20the%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20public%20health%20is%20the%20sole%20criterion%20on%20which%20countries%20vote%2C%20Acharya%20will%20absolutely%20win%2C%20but%20when%20the%20other%20candidate%20is%20the%20daughter%20of%20a%20prime%20minister%2C%20it%20is%20not%20an%20equal%20battle%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspaper%20quoted%20a%20signatory%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20an%20expert%20also%20expressed%20surprise%20at%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccoordinated%20campaign%E2%80%9D%20against%20Wazed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSurprised%20to%20see%20a%20well-coordinated%20negative%20campaign%20going%20on%20against%20Bangladesh(%E2%80%98s)%20candidate%20for%20WHO%20SEAR%20RD%20%E2%80%A6%2C%E2%80%9D%20Monir%20Islam%2C%20former%20WHO%20representative%20in%20Thailand%20and%20Namibia%20and%20former%20director%20of%20health%20systems%20development%20at%20the%20WHO%2C%20Geneva%2C%20wrote%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Southeast%20Asia%20Region%20of%20the%20WHO%20has%20many%20complex%20public%20health%20problems%20to%20tackle.%20The%20countries%20in%20this%20region%20have%20the%20highest%20burden%20of%20some%20of%20the%20diseases%20which%20are%20major%20challenges%20for%20the%20WHO.%20And%2C%20therefore%2C%20an%20expert%20in%20public%20health%2C%20whosoever%20becomes%20head%20of%20this%20regional%20office%20of%20the%20WHO%2C%20will%20have%20a%20lot%20to%20deal%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695460445000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23144006%2Fimage-1349.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fwho-southeast-asia-post-health-experts-worried-over-indias-support-for-sheikh-hasinas-daughter%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20least%2060%20public%20health%20experts%20have%20written%20to%20the%20UN%20agency%20demanding%20more%20transparency%20in%20the%20process.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fwho-southeast-asia-post-health-experts-worried-over-indias-support-for-sheikh-hasinas-daughter%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SRK's%20reply%20to%20a%20fan%20standing%20outside%20Mannat%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695459248000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103886560%2Cimgsize-35148.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fshah-rukh-khan-gives-a-hilarious-reply-to-a-fan-standing-outside-mannat%2Farticleshow%2F103886560.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103886560.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EShah%20Rukh%20Khan%2C%20who%20is%20getting%20praised%20for%20his%20latest%20release%20'Jawan'%2C%20did%20an%20%23AskSRK%20session%20on%20Friday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fshah-rukh-khan-gives-a-hilarious-reply-to-a-fan-standing-outside-mannat%2Farticleshow%2F103886560.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Modi%20Government%20Must%20Answer%20for%20its%20Exploitative%20Fuel%20Price%20Policy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F01083024%2F2022_3img29_Mar_2022_PTI03_29_2022_000081B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20analysis%20has%20been%20undertaken%20by%20members%20of%20the%20InfoSphere%20team%20of%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20To%20review%20their%20previous%20work%2C%20please%20visit%20the%20website%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20write%20to%20the%20team%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Acnes%40jgu.edu.in%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ecnes%40jgu.edu.in%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20high%20inflation%20problem%20over%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years%20%E2%80%93%20anchored%20by%20a%20consistent%20fuel%20price%20hike%20%E2%80%93%20is%20embedded%20in%20an%20act%20of%20price%20collusion%20observed%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20and%20the%20oil%20companies%2C%20who%20were%20importing%20cheaper%20crude%20oil%20(when%20it%20was%20made%20available).%20These%20companies%20profit%20from%20this%20practice%2C%20making%20the%20Indian%20consumers%20pay%20for%20a%20high%20retail%20price%20for%20fuel%20along%20with%20the%20windfall%20gain%20made%20in%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20has%20been%20highlighted%20in%20the%20evidence%20produced%20by%20economists%20like%20Isabella%20Weber%20in%20Europe%20%E2%80%93%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20case%20isn%E2%80%99t%20too%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20unfortunate%20reality%20of%20price%20collusion%20when%20the%20underlying%20market%20conditions%20remain%20oligopolistic%20(where%20few%20dominant%20market%20players%20determine%20the%20selling%20price%20of%20a%20commodity)%20allowed%20firms%20in%20manufacturing%20and%20services%20to%20work%20in%20tandem%20with%20the%20government%20that%20seems%20comfortable%20in%20letting%20firms%20to%20profit%20from%20the%20price%20divergence%20(in%20volatile%20priced%20commodities%20like%20oil)%20without%20passing%20any%20dividends%20to%20the%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20kept%20tax%20on%20fuel%20hiked%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20imported%20price%20of%20crude%20oil%20was%20collapsing%20all%20over%20the%20world.%20Even%20during%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%2C%20the%20benefits%20of%20imported%20cheaper%20Russian%20crude%20oil%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20passed%20over%20to%20the%20retail%20sale%20price%20of%20fuel.%20This%20made%20the%20overall%20inflation%20rate%20to%20continuously%20remain%20high%2C%20even%20when%20food%20inflation%20was%20moderate%20(which%20now%20is%20peaking%20because%20of%20ineffective%20monsoon%20and%20other%20supply-side%20concerns).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20determines%20India%E2%80%99s%20fuel%20prices%3F%20Are%20the%20global%20market%20geopolitical%20considerations%20really%20to%20blame%20for%20the%20high%20costs%20consumers%20have%20to%20bear%3F%20Not%20really%2C%20is%20the%20answer%20%E2%80%93%20and%20below%20we%E2%80%99ll%20break%20down%20why.%20Here%20are%20the%20key%20takeaways%20from%20the%20energy%20woes%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20handling%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrowing%20demand%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20seen%20its%20import%20demand%20of%20oil%20growing%20steadily%20over%20the%20last%20several%20years%2C%20with%20import%20of%20crude%20oil%20and%20other%20petroleum%20products%20nearly%20tripling%20in%20volume%20between%202014%20and%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20growing%20demand%20for%20energy%20has%20also%20been%20observed%20in%20the%20composition%20of%20merchandise%20imports%20between%20the%20same%20period%2C%20with%20imports%20of%20oil%20products%20nearly%20doubling%20in%20value%20from%20Rs%2078%2C281%20crore%20in%20April%202014%20to%20Rs%201%2C68%2C226%20crore%20in%20July%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23125330%2Fimage-1343.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22610%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23125330%2Fimage-1343.png%20610w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23125330%2Fimage-1343-300x248.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674473%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22505%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20CNES-InfoSphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGovernment%20revenues%20%E2%80%93%20more%20for%20the%20Union%20government%20than%20the%20states%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fmarkets%2Fcommodities%2Fnews%2Fcrude-oil-tanks-to-70-but-cut-in-pump-prices-unlikely-soon%2Farticleshow%2F98845419.cms%5C%22%3Eglobal%20oil%20prices%20have%20been%20falling%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20in%20India%2C%20the%20government%20has%20contained%20the%20prices%20of%20oil%20products%20such%20as%20petrol%20and%20diesel%20in%20a%20narrow%20band%20using%20its%20taxation%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20tax%20component%20in%20the%20prices%20of%20motor%20spirits%20has%20been%20a%20major%20source%20of%20revenue%20for%20the%20Union%20government.%20Taxes%20on%20oil%20and%20petroleum%20products%20form%20a%20major%20part%20of%20the%20retail%20prices%20borne%20by%20the%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20take%20the%20example%20of%20Delhi.%20Of%20the%20current%20retail%20price%20of%20petrol%20(Rs%2096.72)%20and%20diesel%20(Rs%2089.62)%2C%20excise%20and%20VAT%20take%20up%2036%25%20and%2031%25%20of%20the%20prices%2C%20respectively.%20At%20the%20height%20of%20rising%20energy%20prices%20in%20late%20October%202021%2C%20this%20share%20used%20to%20be%2054%25%20and%2049%25%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOf%20this%2C%20central%20excise%20duties%20held%20a%20larger%20share%20than%20that%20of%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20VAT%2C%20which%20was%20calculated%20on%20a%20percentage%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23132027%2Fimage-1345.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23132027%2Fimage-1345.png%201000w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23132027%2Fimage-1345-300x212.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674477%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22708%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECentral%20excise%20duties%20held%20a%20larger%20share%20than%20that%20of%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20VAT%2C%20which%20was%20calculated%20on%20a%20percentage%20basis%2C%20from%20January%202014%20to%20January%202023.%20Source%3A%20CNES-InfoSphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20keeps%20a%20fixed%20rate%20of%20excise%20duties%20on%20the%20base%20price%20of%20petrol%20and%20diesel%2C%20which%20has%20contributed%20to%20an%20increasing%20dependence%20on%20the%20revenues%20from%20such%20duties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20total%20tax%20contribution%20from%20the%20petroleum%20sector%20to%20the%20exchequer%2C%20excise%20duties%20levied%20from%20petrol%20and%20diesel%20has%20accounted%20for%20nearly%2075-90%25%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years%20(for%20state%20governments%2C%20VAT%20from%20petrol%20and%20diesel%20has%20accounted%20for%2085-95%25%20during%20the%20same%20period).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20the%20price%20is%20decided%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20prices%20of%20both%20diesel%20and%20petrol%20were%20determined%20by%20the%20Administered%20Price%20Mechanism%20till%202002%2C%20under%20which%20the%20objectives%20of%20stability%20and%20protection%20of%20consumers%20were%20pursued.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20this%20mechanism%20was%20discontinued%2C%20efforts%20were%20directed%20by%20the%20government-run%20Oil%20Marketing%20Companies%20(OMCs)%20like%20IOCL%2C%20HPCL%20and%20BPCL%20to%20maintain%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20consumers%20at%20a%20priority.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20brief%20stint%20of%20market-determined%20prices%2C%20the%20OMCs%20have%20taken%20up%20the%20mantle%20since%202014%20to%20revise%20the%20fuel%20rates%20daily%2C%20by%20considering%20the%20crude%20oil%20prices%20in%20the%20international%20markets%20and%20the%20rupee-dollar%20exchange%20rate.%20As%20prices%20surged%20during%20the%20height%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20years%2C%20profits%20experienced%20by%20these%20companies%20also%20experienced%20a%20spike%2C%20only%20coming%20to%20a%20halt%20when%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fenergy%2Foil-gas%2Foil-firms-govt-are-earning-well-but-you-may-still-have-to-pay-high-fuel-prices%2Farticleshow%2F102160771.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Eprice%20freeze%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20implemented%20despite%20rising%20costs%20in%20early%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20prices%20of%20petrol%20and%20diesel%20have%20hovered%20around%20Rs%20100%2C%20despite%20the%20cut%20in%20excise%20duties%2C%20it%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20how%20the%20oncoming%20production%20cut%20will%20be%20managed%20by%20the%20government.%20Leading%20up%20to%20the%20general%20elections%20of%202024%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2Fwhy-is-opec-cutting-oil-output-2023-05-30%2F%5C%22%3E%20OPEC%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20cut%20production%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20certainly%20not%20bode%20well%20for%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20fuel%20import%20bill.%20Also%2C%20with%20the%20dollar%20exchange%20rate%20already%20at%20record%20high%20despite%20RBI%20intervention%2C%20and%20inflation%20already%20high%2C%20the%20incoming%20rise%20in%20fuel%20costs%20is%20surely%20expected%20to%20exacerbate%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20playbook%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20narrative%20projected%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20in%20managing%20the%20headline%20fuel%20inflation%20is%20also%20interesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20first%20allows%20the%20price%20of%20retail%20petrol%20and%20diesel%2C%20much%20like%20LPG%2C%20to%20rise%2C%20citing%20%E2%80%98external%20factors%20and%20geopolitical%20concerns%E2%80%99.%20This%20allows%20the%20government%20to%20boost%20revenues%2C%20and%20oil%20companies%20to%20make%20abnormal%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flpg-price-cut-modis-rakhi-gift-ends-up-drawing-attention-to-inflation%5C%22%3ELPG%20Price%20Cut%3A%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Rakhi%20%E2%80%98Gift%E2%80%99%20Ends%20up%20Drawing%20Attention%20to%20Inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20the%20government%20either%20does%20not%20increase%20the%20prices%20or%20keeps%20the%20prices%20lower%2C%20marginally%2C%20usually%20when%20it%E2%80%99s%20nearing%20an%20election%20cycle.%20They%20attribute%20these%20efforts%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20who%20is%20allegedly%20working%20to%20bring%20down%20the%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECutting%20through%20the%20fog%20of%20this%20disinformation%2C%20unmasking%20the%20truth%20behind%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20to%20fuel%20is%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20is%20that%20high%20excise%20in%20the%20period%20of%20high%20domestic%20prices%2C%20despite%20record%20low%20prices%20on%20international%20crude%2C%20means%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20already%20made%20a%20high%20windfall%20gain%20in%20excise%20tax%20revenue%20which%20should%20enable%20the%20consumers%20to%20not%20%E2%80%98pay%20for%E2%80%99%20high%20international%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESee%20below%20the%20profit%20and%20loss%20levels%20of%20major%20OMCs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23140244%2Fimage-1346.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22975%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23140244%2Fimage-1346.png%20975w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23140244%2Fimage-1346-300x218.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674483%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22708%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20CNES-InfoSphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20hitting%20rock%20bottom%20post-2022%2C%20companies%20have%20recorded%20profits%20consistently%20from%20thereon.%20If%20we%20look%20at%20the%20relationship%20between%20headline%20inflation%20and%20crude%20oil%20price%2C%20in%20the%20figure%20below%2C%20one%20will%20see%20how%20between%202018%20and%20early%202023%2C%20inflation%20remained%20high%20despite%20a%20gap%20in%20oil%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23140357%2Fimage-1347.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%2