mitments%20on%20a%20range%20of%20issues%20from%20Indo-Pacific%20to%20terrorism%20and%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20was%20represented%20by%20External%20Affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%2C%20who%20arrived%20in%20New%20York%20on%20Friday%20to%20kick-start%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37143%2FVisit_of_External_Affairs_Minister_to_the_United_States_of_America_September_2230_2023%5C%22%3Eweek%20of%20meetings%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20annual%20jamboree.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fbilateral-documents.htm%3Fdtl%2F37144%2FJoint_Readout_of_the_Quad_Foreign_Ministers_Meeting%5C%22%3EAs%20per%20the%20joint%20readout%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Quad%20ministers%20reaffirmed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cinternational%20law%2C%20respect%20for%20sovereignty%20and%20territorial%20integrity%2C%20and%20the%20maintenance%20of%20peace%20and%20security%20in%20the%20maritime%20domain%20underpin%20the%20development%20and%20prosperity%20of%20the%20Indo-Pacific%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECalling%20for%20disputes%20to%20be%20resolved%20peacefully%2C%20the%20Quad%20reiterated%20the%20importance%20of%20adhering%20to%20the%20UN%20Convention%20on%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20Sea%20(UNCLOS)%20to%20address%20maritime%20claims%20in%20the%20South%20And%20East%20China%20Seas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20emphasise%20the%20importance%20of%20adherence%20to%20international%20law%2C%20particularly%20as%20reflected%20in%20the%20United%20Nations%20Convention%20on%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20Sea%20(UNCLOS)%2C%20to%20address%20challenges%20to%20the%20global%20maritime%20rules-based%20order%2C%20including%20with%20respect%20to%20maritime%20claims%2C%20and%20in%20the%20South%20and%20East%20China%20Seas.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20sentence%20is%20nearly%20identical%20to%20the%20one%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2023%2F05%2F20%2Fquad-leaders-joint-statement%2F%5C%22%3EQuad%20Leaders%20joint%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20May%2C%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20the%20newly%20introduced%20term%20%E2%80%9Cincluding%20with%20respect%20to%20maritime%20claims%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffor-the-first-time-india-calls-for-abiding-by-the-2016-arbitral-award-on-south-china-sea%5C%22%3EEarlier%20in%20June%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%20has%20changed%20its%20position%20and%20called%20for%20abiding%20by%20the%20Arbitral%20Tribunal%E2%80%99s%202016%20order%20that%20had%20struck%20down%20China%E2%80%99s%20territorial%20claims%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea.%20The%20Arbitral%20Tribunal%20was%20set%20up%20as%20per%20provisions%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fdepts%2Flos%2Fconvention_agreements%2Ftexts%2Funclos%2Fannex7.htm%5C%22%3EUNCLOS%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20change%20in%20posture%20was%20mentioned%20in%20the%20India-Philippines%20joint%20statement%20issued%20after%20the%20meeting%20of%20the%20fifth%20Joint%20Commission%20on%20bilateral%20cooperation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20joint%20press%20release%20also%20said%20that%20the%20group%20is%20%E2%80%9Ccommitted%20to%20countering%20terrorism%20in%20all%20its%20forms%20and%20manifestations%2C%20including%20preventing%20the%20international%20and%20cross%20border%20movement%20of%20terrorists%2C%20and%20countering%20terror%20finance%20networks%20and%20safe%20havens%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20Quad%20ministers%20%E2%80%9Cstressed%20the%20need%20for%20a%20comprehensive%20and%20balanced%20approach%20to%20effectively%20curb%20terrorist%20activities%20through%20the%20whole%20of%20nation%20and%20whole%20of%20international%20community%20efforts%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EA%20warm%20discussion%20with%20Quad%20colleagues%20to%20start%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FUNGA78%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23UNGA78%3C%2Fa%3E%20participation.%20Welcomed%20Japanese%20FM%20Yoko%20Kamikawa%20to%20the%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDiscussed%20defending%20the%20rules-based%20international%20order%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20and%20delivering%20on%20Quad%20commitments.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlways%20value%20our%20collective%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fg1pDdIpQ8e%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2Fg1pDdIpQ8e%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Dr.%20S.%20Jaishankar%20(%40DrSJaishankar)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDrSJaishankar%2Fstatus%2F1705212023171141740%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%2022%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20Quad%20summit%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20held%20in%20India%2C%20but%20the%20readout%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20refer%20to%20the%20meeting.%20It%2C%20however%2C%20notes%20that%20Japan%20will%20host%20the%20next%20in-person%20foreign%20ministers%20meeting%20in%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20sent%20informal%20feelers%20to%20all%20the%20Quad%20members%20to%20see%20if%20their%20leaders%20would%20be%20available%20to%20be%20the%20chief%20guest%20for%20the%20Republic%20Day%20parade.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20still%20uncertainty%20as%20Australia%20celebrates%20January%2026%20as%20the%20national%20day%20and%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister%20has%20a%20scheduling%20conflict%20with%20the%20parliamentary%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20ambassador%20to%20India%20Eric%20Garcetti%20confirmed%20that%20India%20had%20given%20an%20invitation%20to%20President%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20but%20demurred%20when%20asked%20about%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Quad%20leaders.%20He%2C%20however%2C%20did%20not%20indicate%20that%20the%20invitation%20has%20been%20accepted%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Quad%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20met%20in%20the%20shadow%20of%20the%20explosive%20allegation%20made%20by%20Canadian%20prime%20minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fcanadian-pm-justin-trudeau-reiterates-allegations-of-indias-role-in-sikh-leaders-murder%5C%22%3Einvolvement%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%2C%20who%20is%20described%20as%20a%20pro-Khalistan%20terrorist%20by%20the%20Indian%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20Australia%20had%20both%20termed%20the%20allegations%20as%20%E2%80%9Cserious%E2%80%9D%20and%20urged%20India%20to%20join%20the%20investigations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20dismissed%20the%20allegations%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmotivated%20and%20absurd%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20and%20termed%20Canada%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csafe%20haven%20for%20terrorists%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20Quad%20ministers%20expressed%20%E2%80%9Cdeep%20concern%E2%80%9D%20over%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20and%20urged%20the%20need%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Ca%20comprehensive%2C%20just%2C%20and%20lasting%20peace%20in%20Ukraine%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20international%20law%2C%20consistent%20with%20the%20principles%20of%20the%20UN%20Charter%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20norm%2C%20the%20four%20countries%20also%20said%20that%20use%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%20or%20the%20threat%20of%20use%20was%20unacceptable%20and%20called%20for%20respect%20of%20territorial%20integrity%20and%20sovereignty%20of%20all%20states.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20deeply%20concerned%20about%20the%20global%20food%20security%20situation%20and%20support%20the%20efforts%20of%20the%20UN%20in%20the%20resumption%20of%20the%20Black%20Sea%20Grain%20Initiative%20(BSGI)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20joint%20readout%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695447084000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23105441%2Fimage-1340.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fquad-says-that-all-maritime-claims-should-be-addressed-under-unclos%22%2